This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing tasks, specifically neural machine translation, which falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a new type of neural network architecture, the Recurrent Highway Network, which falls under the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of deep learning models, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores the use of attention mechanisms, which falls under the category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses a dataset of images and text, which could potentially fall under the category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
